b'Hospice and Palliative Medicine Fellowship Program'
b'Home'
b'Education'
b'Graduate Medical Education (GME)'
b'caherman'
b'Hospice and Palliative Medicine Fellowship Program'
b'The first fellow joining the program in 2018 is Harneet K. Gahley, MD. Dr. Gahley is a graduate of American University of Antigua College of Medicine and recently completed a family medicine residency through the University of Illinois College of Medicine Rockford\xe2\x80\x99s Dixon Rural Training Track.'
b'The Hospice and Palliative Medicine Fellowship Program\xc2\xa0sponsored by University of Illinois College of Medicine Rockford is\xc2\xa0accredited by the Accreditation Council for Graduate Medical Education (ACGME).'
b'SwedishAmerican Health System in Rockford serves as the main teaching campus for the program. In addition, Monroe Clinic and Hospital in Monroe, Wis.,\xc2\xa0UW Health in Madison, Wis., Serenity Hospice and Home in Oregon, Ill., and numerous community agencies comprise a comprehensive clinical experience that covers all aspects of palliative care across the continuum.'
b'One fellowship position is available per year and the program participates in the Electronic Residency Application Services (ERAS) and The Match.'
b'For more information, please call the Office of Graduate Medical Education at (815) 395-5753.'
